Question 1. Write a program in PHP using a ‘for’ loop to add all the integers
between 0 and 50 and display the total.

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>

<?php
$x = 0; //Uses variable x
for($y=1;$y<50;$y++){ //Uses variable y and condition check
$c = $x + $y; //Uses variable c
echo "$x + $y = $c"."<br>";
$x = $c; //Set variable x in value of variable c
}
?>

</body>
</html>

Question 2. Write a PHP program to check if a person is eligible to vote using
control structure. (Criteria: Minimum age required to vote is 18)

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>
<?php
$age = 9; //Uses variable age
echo "You are $age years old!"."<br>";
if ($age >= 18){ //True or false
echo "You are eligible to vote!"; //If true 
}else{
echo "You are not eligible to vote!"; // If false
}
?>

</body>
</html>

Question 3. Write a PHP program to check whether a number is prime or not.

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>
<?php
$number = 8; //Uses varibiable
$div1 = $number/1; //Uses varibiable
$remainder = $number%2; //Uses varibiable

if ($div1 == $number and $remainder != 0){ //Check if true
echo "$number is a prime number!"."<br>"; //If true
}else{
echo "$number is not a prime number!"; // if false
}
?>
</body>
